HEADWORD: Nervation
<hw>Ner*va"tion</hw> <pr>(n⟦etil⟧r*v⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>The arrangement of nerves and veins, especially those of leaves;
neuration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The outlines of the fronds of ferns, and their
<qex>nervation</qex>, are frail characters if employed alone for the
determination of existing genera.</q> <rj><qau>J. D.
Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nerve</ent>⟦br⟧
